  "course_description": "Honors research in Latin under the direct supervision of a faculty member. Open by invitation only.",
  "course_notes": "Standard economic models assume people are perfectly rational. They're not - and it matters. This course explores what happens to markets, prices, and financial decisions when real human behavior - biases, short-sightedness, overconfidence, and social pressure - enters the picture. You'll run experiments, analyze real market data, and learn frameworks that apply directly to careers in finance, consulting, product design, and policy - and to your own financial life.",
